main event: A UFO was tracked on radar for approximately 1 hour and 54 minutes over Goose Bay, Labrador, Canada.
interesting points: The object was detected on three separate radar sites,The trajectory showed several loops and dips, indicating erratic behavior,Visual observation was not possible due to overcast skies,The object was tracked at altitudes varying from 5,000 to 13,000 feet,Two fighters attempted interception but made no visual contact.
sighted object: One unidentified flying object tracked on radar
witness description: Military personnel, considered reliable, including pilots and radar operators
